Q1 A. BadStore's Cart Cookie – Which field gives a discount?
================================================================================

ANSWER: Field 3 (the Price field)

DETAILED STEPS:
---------------
1. Start the BadStore virtual machine and ensure it is accessible on your network.
   Note down its IP address (e.g., 192.168.56.101).

2. Open a browser (preferably Firefox) and navigate to:
      http://192.168.56.101/

3. Register or log in with any account credentials.

4. Browse the store, click on any item, and add it to the cart using the
   "Add to Cart" button.

5. Once an item is in the cart, you need to read the cart cookie.
   Go to the Search box on the BadStore homepage.

6. In the search box, type the following XSS payload and press Enter:
      <script>alert(document.cookie)</script>

7. A browser alert dialog will pop up showing all active cookies.
   You will see something like:
      SSOid=abc123; CartID=1527258326%3A1%3A11.5%3A1000

8. Copy the CartID value: 1527258326%3A1%3A11.5%3A1000

9. URL-decode it using https://www.urldecoder.org
   Paste the value and click Decode.
   Result: 1527258326:1:11.5:1000

10. Analyze the decoded cookie fields (separated by colons):
      - Field 1: 1527258326  → Unix timestamp (when cart was created)
      - Field 2: 1           → Quantity of item
      - Field 3: 11.5        → Price of item  ← THIS IS THE TARGET
      - Field 4: 1000        → Item ID

11. To exploit: URL-encode a modified cookie where Field 3 is set to a
    very small value, e.g., 0.01
      Modified: 1527258326:1:0.01:1000
      URL-encoded: 1527258326%3A1%3A0.01%3A1000

12. Use browser developer tools (F12 → Application → Cookies) or a cookie
    editor extension to set CartID to the modified value.

13. Proceed to checkout — the price charged will now be the modified amount.

ANSWER SUMMARY: Field 3 (price) is the field an attacker changes to get
a discount.

