Q10 A. Scapy – Identify Hosts Up in Local Network using ARP
================================================================================

CODE (save as arp_host_discover.py):
--------------------------------------
   from scapy.all import *

   # Step 1: Define the subnet to scan
   # Find your subnet with: ip addr show
   # Example: if your IP is 192.168.1.50/24, subnet is 192.168.1.0/24
   target_subnet = "192.168.1.0/24"

   print(f"Scanning {target_subnet} for live hosts...")
   print("This may take a few seconds...\n")

   # Step 2: Craft Ethernet broadcast + ARP Request
   # Ether(dst="ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff") = send to ALL devices on LAN
   # ARP(pdst=...) = asking "Who has this IP? Tell me your MAC."
   arp_request = Ether(dst="ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff") / ARP(pdst=target_subnet)

   # Step 3: Send at Layer 2 and capture responses
   # srp() = send + receive, works at Ethernet level
   # timeout=2 → wait up to 2 seconds for all replies
   # verbose=False → suppress Scapy's default output
   answered, unanswered = srp(arp_request, timeout=2, verbose=False)

   # Step 4: Display all hosts that replied
   print(f"{'Host IP':<20} {'MAC Address'}")
   print("=" * 40)
   for sent, received in answered:
       print(f"{received.psrc:<20} {received.hwsrc}")

   print(f"\nTotal live hosts found: {len(answered)}")
   print(f"Non-responding IPs:    {len(unanswered)}")

