Q12 A. Scapy – Display Route and Measure Transit Delays (Traceroute)
================================================================================

(Same as Q3 A / Q11 A — Traceroute to www.example.com and www.google.com)

CODE (save as traceroute_delay.py):
-------------------------------------
   from scapy.all import *

   # traceroute() works by sending UDP or ICMP packets with TTL starting at 1
   # Each router decrements TTL; when TTL=0, it sends ICMP TTL Exceeded back
   # By recording which router responds at each TTL, we reconstruct the path
   # RTT (Round Trip Time) for each hop shows transit delay

   targets = ["www.example.com", "www.google.com"]
   print(f"Tracerouting to: {targets}\n")

   result, unanswered = traceroute(targets, maxttl=20, verbose=1)

   print("\n===== Route and Delay Summary =====")
   result.show()

